I used to cut out my patterns by hand, but it took forever, and was just annoying to do. I tried foil shears, but they're even worse, so now I have my cricut machine do it for me!

Patterns that I plan to reuse over and over get cut out of cardstock, and some larger projects I'll use pvc-free vinyl. I always design my patterns in Photoshop at 300dpi with 10px lines, then I import the pattern into the cricut app (I always need to resize the image in there, but that's not a big deal), and what comes out is a perfectly cut pattern that leaves just enough space for foil.

#artprocess #cricut #stainedglass #pattern #patternmaking #howto

I felt super productive this week - such a great feeling! What do we think of glow in the dark glass? I think it's super cool, but definitely a novelty. The glass is charged by the sun, and the glow is pretty subtle once the sun finally sets. To get the maximum effect from the glow glass here, I just shined a black light on it for a couple seconds, and that instantly charged it.
